Lakers End Talks on Acquiring Paul to Pursue Howard Instead, ESPN Reports

-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 
2011-12-11T13:38:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/lakers-withdraw-from-chris-paul-trade-talks-will-target-howard-espn-says.html
The Los Angeles Lakers withdrew from
trade talks regarding New Orleans Hornets All-Star point guard
 Chris Paul  and instead will target Orlando Magic center  Dwight
Howard , ESPN reported, citing people familiar with the
situation.  The Lakers will also send forward Lamar Odom to the Dallas
Mavericks for a National Basketball Association first-round
draft pick, the people told ESPN.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  